y of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Alice Bracton was born in 1385, her father, Sir John Bracton II, was 26 and her mother, Lady Lillian Bolleyn, was 27. She married Sir Geoffrey Boleyn I in 1400, in Salle, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1440, in Blickling, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 55, and was buried in Salle, Norfolk, England."},"et":{"1385–1440":"1385–1440","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1403–1472":"1403–1472","1406–1463":"1406–1463","1408–1458":"1408–1458","1412–1470":"1412–1470","1414–1470":"1414–1470","1420–1485":"1420–1485","1359–1410":"1359–1410","1358–1410":"1358–1410","1385":"1385","1440":"1440","1472":"1472","1383":"1383","1470":"1470","1380":"1380","1403":"1403","1414":"1414","1359":"1359","1458":"1458","1358":"1358","1412":"1412","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1485":"1485","1463":"1463","about 1420":"umbes 1420","1408":"1408","1406":"1406","Salle, Norfolk, England":"Salle, Norfolk, England","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Newenden, Kent, England":"Newenden, Kent, England","St. Peter and St. Paul's Churchyard, Salle, Norfolk, England":"Salle, Norfolk, England","Blickling, Norfo